---
import BaseLayout from "../layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
import NavBar from "../components/NavBar.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<BaseLayout
  title="About the Community – First Ballston Commons"
  description="Learn about First Ballston Commons: a close-knit Ballston neighborhood with brick townhomes, commuter-friendly transit, and community-minded homeowners."
  canonical="/about-the-community"
>
  <NavBar />

  <section class="relative overflow-hidden bg-slate-900 pt-20 text-white">
    <img
      src="/assets/banner.avif"
      alt="Brick townhomes in the First Ballston Commons community"
      class="absolute inset-0 h-full w-full object-cover"
      loading="eager"
      decoding="async"
      fetchpriority="high"
    />
    <div class="hero-overlay absolute inset-0 z-10"></div>
    <div class="relative z-20 mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4 py-14 md:py-20">
      <div class="max-w-3xl space-y-4">
        <h1 class="text-4xl leading-tight font-extrabold md:text-5xl">About the Community</h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-white/90">
          Experience the perfect blend of urban convenience and neighborhood charm.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="bg-background-light grow">
    <section class="py-12">
      <div class="mx-auto max-w-6xl px-4">
        <article class="overflow-hidden rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-white shadow-lg">
          <div class="space-y-10 p-6 md:p-10">
            <section class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <h2 class="m-0 text-3xl font-bold">Welcome to First Ballston Commons</h2>
              </div>
              <p class="mb-6 text-lg text-slate-700">
                Nestled in the heart of Arlington, Virginia, First Ballston Commons is a vibrant
                townhome community that perfectly balances urban convenience with neighborhood
                charm. Our community is characterized by its friendly atmosphere, well-maintained
                grounds, and engaged residents who take pride in their homes.
              </p>
              <div
                class="rounded-r-lg border-l-4 border-blue-500 bg-blue-50 p-6 dark:bg-blue-900/20"
              >
                <p class="text-gray-700 italic dark:text-gray-300">
                  "A quiet, connected community with reserved parking, attentive upkeep, and
                  neighbors who look out for each other."
                </p>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span
                  class="inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-green-100 text-2xl text-green-600 dark:bg-green-900/40 dark:text-green-400"
                >
                  <span class="material-symbols-outlined leading-none">park</span>
                </span>
                <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Community Background</h2>
              </div>
              <p class="mb-4 leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
                Established in the mid-1980s, First Ballston Commons was designed to offer spacious
                living within walking distance of the Ballston Metro corridor. The architecture
                reflects a classic brick aesthetic that harmonizes with the historic character of
                Arlington County while providing modern amenities.
              </p>
              <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
                Over the decades, we have evolved into a diverse community of young professionals,
                families, and long-term residents, creating a unique tapestry of experiences and
                backgrounds.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span
                  class="inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-orange-100 text-2xl text-orange-600 dark:bg-orange-900/40 dark:text-orange-400"
                >
                  <span class="material-symbols-outlined leading-none">home</span>
                </span>
                <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900">The Townhomes</h2>
              </div>
              <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
                Our residences feature multi-level layouts, private patios, and reserved parking
                spaces directly in front of each unit. The community takes pride in maintaining a
                cohesive aesthetic while allowing for individual expression within our architectural
                guidelines.
              </p>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span
                  class="inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-blue-100 text-2xl text-blue-600 dark:bg-blue-900/40 dark:text-blue-400"
                >
                  <span class="material-symbols-outlined leading-none">place</span>
                </span>
                <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Location & Convenience</h2>
              </div>
              <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
                First Ballston Commons is located in a well-connected part of Arlington with
                convenient access to public transit, biking infrastructure, parks, schools,
                libraries, and neighborhood amenities.
              </p>
              <ul class="list-none space-y-4 pl-0">
                <li class="relative pl-6">
                  <span class="bg-primary absolute top-1 left-0 mt-1 h-2 w-2 rounded-full"></span>
                  <strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Metro:</strong> The community is within
                  walking distance of the Ballston–MU Metro Station on the Orange and Silver lines, providing
                  direct access to Washington, D.C. and other areas of Northern Virginia.
                </li>
                <li class="relative pl-6">
                  <span class="bg-primary absolute top-1 left-0 mt-1 h-2 w-2 rounded-full"></span>
                  <strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Bus Service:</strong> Several ART and
                  Metrobus routes operate nearby along Wilson Boulevard and Fairfax Drive, offering regular
                  service throughout Arlington and to surrounding neighborhoods.
                </li>
                <li class="relative pl-6">
                  <span class="bg-primary absolute top-1 left-0 mt-1 h-2 w-2 rounded-full"></span>
                  <strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Biking and Trails:</strong> Residents
                  have access to Arlington's bike network, including nearby connections to the Custis
                  Trail, which links Ballston to Rosslyn and regional trail systems. Bike lanes and shared-use
                  paths support both commuting and recreational cycling.
                </li>
                <li class="relative pl-6">
                  <span class="bg-primary absolute top-1 left-0 mt-1 h-2 w-2 rounded-full"></span>
                  <strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Parks and Amenities:</strong><ul
                    class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5"
                  >
                    <li>
                      Quincy Park is a short walk from the community and includes open green space,
                      athletic fields, courts, and a playground.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Ballston Quarter is within walking distance and provides dining, retail,
                      fitness options, and entertainment.
                    </li>
                    <li>
                      Lubber Run Park, approximately 0.8 miles away, includes wooded trails, picnic
                      areas, playgrounds, and the Lubber Run Amphitheater.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
                <li class="relative pl-6">
                  <span class="bg-primary absolute top-1 left-0 mt-1 h-2 w-2 rounded-full"></span>
                  <strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Library:</strong> Arlington's Central
                  Library, located on Quincy Street near Quincy Park, is within walking distance and offers
                  reading rooms, study and meeting spaces, public programs, and resources for all ages.
                </li>
                <li class="relative pl-6">
                  <span class="bg-primary absolute top-1 left-0 mt-1 h-2 w-2 rounded-full"></span>
                  <strong class="text-gray-900 dark:text-white">Schools:</strong>
                  <ul class="mt-2 list-disc space-y-1 pl-5">
                    <li>
                      Ashlawn Elementary School is approximately 1.4 miles from the community.
                    </li>
                    <li>Swanson Middle School is approximately 1.3 miles away.</li>
                    <li>
                      Washington-Liberty High School is located about 0.3 miles from First Ballston
                      Commons.
                    </li>
                  </ul>
                </li>
              </ul>

              <div
                class="relative h-80 w-full overflow-hidden rounded-lg border border-gray-300 bg-gray-200 shadow-sm dark:border-gray-600 dark:bg-gray-700"
              >
                <iframe
                  allowfullscreen=""
                  class="absolute inset-0 h-full w-full"
                  loading="lazy"
                  referrerpolicy="no-referrer-when-downgrade"
                  src="https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m18!1m12!1m3!1d12423.837894364074!2d-77.12195742417482!3d38.88085429184518!2m3!1f0!2f0!3f0!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x89b7b43a96c34f71%3A0x5e9553759715560a!2sBallston%2C%20Arlington%2C%20VA!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1620000000000!5m2!1sen!2sus"
                  style="border:0;"></iframe>
              </div>
            </section>

            <section class="space-y-4">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
                <span
                  class="inline-flex h-12 w-12 items-center justify-center rounded-lg bg-purple-100 text-2xl text-purple-600 dark:bg-purple-900/40 dark:text-purple-400"
                >
                  <span class="material-symbols-outlined leading-none">groups</span>
                </span>
                <h2 class="m-0 text-2xl font-semibold text-slate-900">Community Association</h2>
              </div>
              <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
                First Ballston Commons is governed by a Homeowners Association (HOA) Board comprised
                of volunteer residents. The Board meets regularly to discuss community maintenance,
                financials, and improvement initiatives.
              </p>
              <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
                The community is professionally managed by <strong
                  >Capital Property Management</strong
                >, which supports day-to-day operations, homeowner communications, and coordination
                of services on behalf of the Association.
              </p>
              <p class="leading-relaxed text-slate-700">
                Residents are encouraged to attend meetings, stay informed, and participate in
                community activities and governance.
              </p>
            </section>

            <div
              class="mt-12 rounded-lg border border-gray-100 bg-gray-50 p-6 text-center dark:border-gray-700 dark:bg-gray-800/50"
            >
              <p class="text-sm text-gray-500 dark:text-gray-400">
                Questions about the community? Feel free to reach out via the <a
                  class="text-primary hover:underline"
                  href="https://engage.goenumerate.com/s/firstballstoncommons/home.php"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener">Resident Portal</a
                > or contact our <a
                  class="text-primary hover:underline"
                  href="https://engage.goenumerate.com/s/firstballstoncommons/hoapage.php?page=contact_17941"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener">management office</a
                >.
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</BaseLayout>

<Footer />
